pr-worktree [PR_NUMBER | JIRA_KEY | --suffix SUFFIX | -s SUFFIX]

Pick a GitHub PR or JIRA issue via fzf and create a sibling git
worktree for it. With no argument, an fzf picker is shown listing,
in this order:

  1. GitHub PRs in the current repo that involve you (opened,
     commented, reviewed, assigned, mentioned).
  2. Your open JIRA issues (assignee/reporter/watcher, not Done) via
     acli. Skipped silently if acli is missing or unauthenticated.
  3. Other open PRs in the repo that don't involve you, so you can
     pick up a teammate's PR for local review.

Selecting a PR creates a worktree at  ../<repo>-pr-<N>  on the PR
branch. Selecting a JIRA issue creates a worktree at  ../<repo>-<KEY>
on a new branch named <KEY> off origin/<default-branch>.

When called with an argument, the picker is skipped:
  - A numeric value is treated as a PR number.
  - A value matching the JIRA key shape (e.g. DATA-1234) is treated
    as a JIRA issue.
  - --suffix SUFFIX (or -s SUFFIX) creates a worktree at
    ../<repo>-<SUFFIX> on a new branch named <SUFFIX> off
    origin/<default-branch>, with no PR or JIRA lookup.

If the target worktree path already exists, it is entered instead of
recreated.

Requires: gh, git, fzf. acli is optional (enables the JIRA rows).
